@rebecca46and2 I don’t mind having different views, I value everyone’s opinion and like to consider what people say when it’s debated in a civilised manner just like this.
I don’t however feel an entire group should ever be judged for the actions of some, wether it’s men, women or religious people.
Only bad people who have done bad things should be hated on, that applies to all walks of life.

@rebecca46and2 I actually like to debate and hear/consider both sides so I’ll answer this of course. But just to make my view clear, I don’t think what Gillette tackled applies to most men, I think it’s a minority and that’s why I’m angry at the add as it implies it’s a widespread issue applying to men in general. 
To answer your question, imagine an advert for tampax which told women they could do better, told them they should not falsely accuse men of rape, that they should not stop kids from seeing their fathers, that they shouldn’t have sex for money or take crack.
We would be up in arms because most women are not like that and we would feel it paints us in the wrong light.
